    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="504"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.62114A/4–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-18T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 18, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 18—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1244. We have received no reply to the Ambassador’s letter to Molotov dated April
                    15, which was sent in compliance with Department’s 864 April 14, noon.<note
                        n="10" xml:id="d504fn10">Telegram 864 not printed, but see telegram 1486,
                        April 14, to Paris, <ref target="#pg_712">p. 712</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Under the circumstances I am informing Foreign Office that we are proceeding with
                    the acceptance of the German proposal insofar as it relates to American
                    prisoners of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
